episodes.title: Beyond Blunderdome
episodes.plot: Convinced he's the only man with guts to tell him the truth, Mel Gibson insists Homer accompanies him in Hollywood to help fix his newest film project.

episodes.title: Brother's Little Helper
episodes.plot: Bart is put on medication to control his behavior, but the pills cause him to become paranoid and insane.

episodes.title: Guess Who's Coming to Criticize Dinner?
episodes.plot: When Homer is hired as a local food critic by a newspaper in Springfield, he finds himself in deep trouble after his reviews turn out to be too critical.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror X
episodes.plot: The Simpsons attempt to cover up their accidental murder of Ned Flanders. Bart and Lisa acquire super powers. An electronic apocalypse threatens Springfield.

episodes.title: E-I-E-I-(Annoyed Grunt)
episodes.plot: Homer cowards out of a pistol-duel and hides out with the rest of the family on a country farm.

episodes.title: Hello Gutter, Hello Fadder
episodes.plot: Homer becomes a minor celebrity around Springfield after bowling a perfect game.

episodes.title: Eight Misbehavin'
episodes.plot: Apu struggles with fatherhood after Manjula gives birth to octuplets.

episodes.title: Take My Wife, Sleaze
episodes.plot: Homer's attempt at creating a motorcycle gang attracts a real gang, who kidnap Marge.

episodes.title: Grift of the Magi
episodes.plot: A toy company purchases Springfield Elementary and uses the student body as a focus group for their new Christmas toy Funzo.

episodes.title: Little Big Mom
episodes.plot: Lisa finds out how rough Marge has it when her mom is in traction and she becomes the woman of the house. Homer and Bart's antics get her so worked up she conspires to teach them a lesson.

episodes.title: Faith Off
episodes.plot: Bart is led to believe he has special healing powers after a tent revival.

episodes.title: The Mansion Family
episodes.plot: Homer receives responsibility for Mr. Burns' mansion when he is on leave and takes Burns' yacht to international waters to have a party.

episodes.title: Saddlesore Galactica
episodes.plot: The Simpsons get an abused horse and make him a contender in horse racing. Homer finds out a secret conspiracy about jockeys. Lisa tries to reach President Clinton when the results of a school band talent competition seem tainted.

episodes.title: Alone Again, Natura-Diddly
episodes.plot: Ned deals with his grief after Maude's untimely death.

episodes.title: Missionary: Impossible
episodes.plot: When Homer is wanted dead for reneging on a 10,000 dollar pledge to PBS, Reverend Lovejoy sets him up for missionary work in the South Pacific until the heat dies down.

episodes.title: Pygmoelian
episodes.plot: Plastic surgery not only transforms Moe the Bartender from ugly to hunky, it helps gets him a job on a hit daytime drama.

episodes.title: Bart to the Future
episodes.plot: Bart gets a glimpse of the future while the family is on vacation at an Indian casino.

episodes.title: Days of Wine and D'oh'ses
episodes.plot: Homer doesn't like it when Barney quits drinking; Bart and Lisa get into trouble when they enter a photo contest for the new phone book cover.

episodes.title: Kill the Alligator and Run
episodes.plot: Fearing he only has three years to live, Homer takes the family on a vacation to Florida, where they become fugitives after seemingly killing a famous alligator.

episodes.title: Last Tap Dance in Springfield
episodes.plot: Lisa has difficulties learning to tap dance; Bart and Milhouse ditch summer camp to spend a week living in the mall.

episodes.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad, Mad Marge
episodes.plot: Everybody loves the new Simpsons' house guest Becky. Except Marge, who thinks Becky wants to kill her.

episodes.title: Behind the Laughter
episodes.plot: Fans are invited to take a behind-the-scenes look at "The Simpsons," revisiting some of the most memorable experiences the family has been through.
